Interface Entry<T>

Type Parameters:
T - the type of the associated value
All Known Implementing Classes:
BatchingHandlerRepository.Update, SearchHit
public interface Entry<T>
Represents a key-value pair with a string-based identifier.

This interface is commonly used in Flux to model lightweight references to domain objects, documents, or indexed values. It is intentionally simple and generic to allow broad reuse across components such as the DocumentStore, HandlerRepository, and other infrastructure abstractions.
